     \"step 0\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"Under this reflection, the point M is mapped to N.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Point M is defined as the common point of the circle centered at G1 through A and the circle centered at G2 through B. Reflection swaps the two circles from the previous step, so it sends their common point M to the corresponding common point N.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"reflection preserves circles and distances\",\n        \"step 1\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The point C is mapped to D under the same reflection.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"C lies on the line through M parallel to AB and on the circle centered at G1 through A. Reflection sends the line through M parallel to AB to the line through N parallel to AB, and it sends the circle centered at G1 through A to the circle centered at G2 through B. Therefore the image of C satisfies exactly the defining conditions of D.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"reflection preserves parallelism\",\n        \"reflection preserves circles and distances\",\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"step 2\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The reflection maps the line AC to the line BD, so the intersection point E of AC and BD is fixed by the reflection.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Since A maps to B and C maps to D, the image of line AC is line BD. The point E is defined as the intersection of these two lines, so its image must be the same intersection point; hence E is fixed.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"image of a line under reflection\",\n        \"intersection of lines\",\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"step 3\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The reflection maps the pair of lines AN and CD to the pair of lines BN and CD, so P is mapped to Q.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By the previous steps, A maps to B, N maps to the corresponding reflected point, and C maps to D. Since P is the intersection of lines AN and CD, its image lies on the reflected line BN and also on CD; thus it is exactly the point Q defined as the intersection of BN and CD.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"reflection preserves incidence\",\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"step 3\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The distances EP and EQ are equal.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Reflection is an isometry, so it preserves distances. Since E is fixed by the reflection and P is mapped to Q, the distance from E to P equals the distance from the image of E to the image of P, namely EQ.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"reflection is an isometry\",\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"step 5\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"EP = EQ\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
