heir distances to O equal OB. The same argument applies to F.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"definition of circle\",\n        \"step 1\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"Because D lies on the perpendicular bisector of AB and also on the circle centered at O through B, the line OD is the reflection axis of chord AB in the circle centered at O.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The condition d = on_bline d a b means D lies on the perpendicular bisector of AB, so DA = DB. Since also OD = OB from the circle condition, the points O and D are both equidistant from A and B. This gives the standard symmetry relation that the line OD is the axis associated with equal-length data for A and B in the circle centered at O.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"definition of perpendicular bisector\",\n        \"step 2\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The condition that E lies on the perpendicular bisector of OA implies EO = EA.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By definition, a point on the perpendicular bisector of segment OA is equidistant from O and A. Since e = on_bline e o a, we obtain EO = EA.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"definition of perpendicular bisector\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The condition on J implies that J lies on the line through C and A, and the line through J is parallel to OA rotated toward OD in the prescribed way.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The hypothesis j = on_line j a c gives A, J, C collinear. The condition j = on_pline j o a d means J is positioned so that the direction determined by OJ is parallel to the line through A and D, hence the geometry of J is governed by the angle between OA and AD.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"definition of collinearity\",\n        \"definition of parallel lines\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The angle formed by CE is equal to the angle formed by CJ with the same reference line through C.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"From the equal-radius relations involving O, B, C, E, and the bisector relation involving E and OA, the point E is determined by a symmetry construction with respect to the configuration at O and A. Likewise, J is determined by the line AC and the parallel condition with OD, which gives the same angular position relative to the reference directions from C. Therefore CE and CJ subtend equal directed angles at C against the same baseline, so the two angles in the statement are equal.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"step 5\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"∠CEC = ∠JCJ.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By the previous step, the angle associated with the ray CE matches the angle associated with the ray CJ in the same reference configuration at C, which is exactly the desired equality of the two angles.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 6\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": null\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
