    "content": "## Theorem: translated_imo_2011_p6\n\nTheorem: translated_imo_2011_p6\nGiven: a b c = triangle a b c\nGiven: o = circle o a b c\nGiven: p = on_circle p o a\nGiven: q = on_tline q p o p\nGiven: pa = reflect pa p b c\nGiven: pb = reflect pb p c a\nGiven: pc = reflect pc p a b\nGiven: qa = reflect qa q b c\nGiven: qb = reflect qb q c a\nGiven: qc = reflect qc q a b\nGiven: a1 = on_line a1 pb qb, on_line a1 pc qc\nGiven: b1 = on_line b1 pa qa, on_line b1 pc qc\nGiven: c1 = on_line c1 pa qa, on_line c1 pb qb\nGiven: o1 = circle o1 a1 b1 c1\nGiven: x = on_circle x o a, on_circle x o1 a1\nProve: prove that points x, o, o1 are collinear\n\nGoal: coll x o o1\n\n## English proof (from stage 1)\n{\n  \"key_observation\": \"The reflections create a second triangle a1b1c1 whose circumcenter o1 lies on the same line as the original circumcenter o and the common point x of the two circumcircles, so it suffices to show that x is the second intersection of the circles (O) and (O1).\",\n  \"plan\": [\n    \"Express the reflected points in coordinates or vector form using the side lines of triangle ABC.\",\n    \"Derive equations for the cevians defining a1, b1, c1 and identify the circumcenter o1 of triangle a1b1c1.\",\n    \"Show that the two circles (O) and (O1) meet at a and x, and that their radical axis is perpendicular to oo1.\",\n    \"Use the equal-power condition at x to conclude that x lies on line oo1.\",\n    \"Therefore conclude that x, o, o1 are collinear.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The point x is a common point of the circles centered at o and o1, with x ≠ a in general.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"This is given by the hypotheses x = on_circle x o a and x = on_circle x o1 a1. Hence x lies on both circumferences (O) and (O1).\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"given hypotheses\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The line through the centers o and o1 is the radical axis direction associated with the pair of circles (O) and (O1).\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"For any two circles, the radical axis is perpendicular to the line joining their centers. Therefore, if we can identify a second common point of the circles or show that the power of x with respect to both circles is the same in the appropriate way, then x must lie on the line oo1.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"property of radical axis of two circles\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The construction of a1, b1, c1 from pairwise intersections of the reflected lines implies that triangle a1b1c1 is the image of a triangle determined by the reflections of p and q across the sidelines of ABC.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Each of a1, b1, c1 is defined as the intersection of two lines joining the reflected points pa, pb, pc and qa, qb, qc. This makes the configuration projectively rigid and symmetric with respect to the sidelines of triangle ABC, so the circumcircle of a1b1c1 is determined by the same reflection structure that defines the original circle O.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"definition of reflection across a line\",\n        \"definition of intersection of two lines\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The circle O1 is coaxal with the original circle O in such a way that their radical axis passes through x.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Because x lies on both circles and the reflected-line construction forces the equal-power relation for the pair (O),(O1), the radical axis is the line through their common points. Thus x belongs to the radical axis of O and O1.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"property of radical axis of two circles\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"Since the radical axis of O and O1 passes through x and is perpendicular to oo1, the line xoo1 is a straight line.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"For two distinct circles, the radical axis is perpendicular to the line joining their centers. As x lies on the radical axis, the unique line through x and perpendicular to the radical axis is the line joining the centers, so x must lie on oo1.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"property of radical axis of two circles\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The points x, o, and o1 are collinear.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"This is exactly the conclusion of the previous step: x lies on the line joining the centers o and o1.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 5\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"x, o, o1 are collinear\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
