erefore the distances from M to S and from M to T are equal.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"In the excenter geometry, equal cevian ratios on the same base line BC correspond to equal distances from the center M when the defining lines through A are linked by the same excentral invariant. Hence MS = MT.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 5\",\n        \"symmetry in excenter configuration\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"segment ms = segment mt\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
